		"description": "<p>This pale white pumpkin is small enough to fit in the palm of a human hand. A macabre, grinning face is carved into one side, and a candle within burns an eerie purple flame. While its candle is lit, this pumpkin lantern shines dim light in a 10-foot radius. The lantern&rsquo;s candle burns for 1 minute, after which the pumpkin instantly rots and loses its magic.</p>\n<p>Undead must make a DC 12 Wisdom saving throw when entering the radius or when beginning their turn within the pumpkin&rsquo;s light, taking 3d6 radiant damage on a failed save or half as much on a success. Incorporeal undead have disadvantage on this saving throw.</p>",
